Chordate:



Chordate sighed in a happy tone.  Feline was still brushing the tip of her 
tail against his neck.  It felt nice.  Listening to what she had to say, he 
smiled back.  "You're welcome." he responded.  That was all he could get out, 
now that Feline had began holding onto his arm tightly and was now closer 
than before.  He sighed happily once more, continuing to walk for the mess 
hall, wishing the moment would last forever.  But, he knew, as soon as the 
computer told him the intruder was on the move, he would have to 
unfortunately go.  "Oh, heh, how silly of me.  My name is Chordate.  What's 
yours?"
